title: Apple
means: a round fruit with red, yellow, or green skin and firm white flesh

title: Cherry
means: a small round fruit that is usually red or black

title: Word
means: a sound or combination of sounds that has a meaning and is spoken or written see also

title: Random
means: without a particular plan or pattern

title: Grape
means: a green, dark red, or purplish-black berry that is used to make wine or is eaten as a fruit see also

title: State
means: a way of living or existing

title: Binding
means: forcing or requiring someone to do something because of a promise, agreement, etc.

title: Class
means: a group of students who meet regularly to be taught a subject or activity

title: View
means: an opinion or way of thinking about something

title: Structure
means: the way that something is built, arranged, or organized

title: Implement
means: to begin to do or use (something, such as a plan)

title: End
means: to stop or finish, to no longer continue to happen or exist

title: Do
means: to perform (an action or activity)

title: Wonderful
means: extremely good

title: Fair
means: agreeing with what is thought to be right or acceptable

title: Even
means: used to stress something that is surprising or unlikely

title: Soon
means: at a time that is not long from now

title: Because
means: for the reason that

title: Of
means: belonging to, relating to, or connected with (someone or something)

title: As
means: used to indicate how a person or thing appears, is thought of, etc.

title: So
means: for that reason, and therefore

title: Before
means: at a time preceding (something or someone)

title: As of
means: used to indicate the time or date when something begins

title: While
means: during the time that

title: That
means: used to introduce a clause that is the subject or object of a verb

title: Teach
means: to cause or help (someone) to learn about a subject by giving lessons

title: Believe
means: to accept or regard (something) as true

title: Anyhow
means: in a way that is not organized or neat, in a careless way

title: Fairly
means: to some degree or extent but not very or extremely, to a reasonable or moderate extent

title: Brave
means: to face or deal with (something dangerous or unpleasant)

title: Peaceful
means: quiet and calm; without noise, excitement, etc.
